            "ratingValue": "2",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I am very disappointed with the school management because there are 48 children in my daughter's class which is class 1. When I asked them how can a teacher take care of 48 children at once, they replied saying they have been doing it for 25 years and they admit upto 60 students in a class.\nI am talking about Ist graders here who have never been to proper school for two years and were attending classes online. These kids don't know how a school or a classroom functions and they need individual attention. But the school isn't bothered clearly. I would have changed the school immediately However we bought the books for the academic year unfortunately. This is atrocious. Very disappointed",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
